name: Los Angeles Regional Food Bank
description: Fights hunger and provides food for those in need throughout Los Angeles County.

name: Homeboy Industries
description: Offers job training, support, and services to formerly gang-involved and previously incarcerated individuals.

name: Los Angeles LGBT Center
description: Provides health, housing, and legal services to the LGBTQ+ community and beyond.

name: Habitat for Humanity of Greater Los Angeles
description: Builds affordable housing and revitalizes neighborhoods in partnership with low-income families.

name: Children's Hospital Los Angeles
description: Provides pediatric healthcare, research, and advocacy to improve the lives of children.

name: Los Angeles Mission
description: Offers emergency shelter, food, and support services to homeless individuals and families.

name: TreePeople
description: Engages communities in tree planting, sustainable urban forest management, and environmental education.

name: United Way of Greater Los Angeles
description: Works to end poverty and homelessness through advocacy and community initiatives.

name: Los Angeles County Museum of Art (LACMA)
description: Preserves and shares art and culture from around the world with the Los Angeles community.

name: Goodwill Southern California
description: Provides job training and employment services to individuals with disabilities and disadvantages.

name: Los Angeles Regional Reentry Partnership
description: A collaborative effort to support formerly incarcerated individuals in their successful reintegration into society.

name: Heal the Bay
description: Protects and improves the health of Southern California's coastal waters and watersheds.

name: Los Angeles Conservancy
description: Preserves and revitalizes historic places throughout Los Angeles County.

name: 826LA
description: Empowers young writers through free writing and tutoring programs.

name: Inner-City Arts
description: Provides arts education and creative experiences to underserved youth in Los Angeles.

name: Los Angeles Mission College Foundation
description: Supports student success and educational initiatives at Los Angeles Mission College.

name: Friends of the Los Angeles River (FoLAR)
description: Advocates for the revitalization and protection of the Los Angeles River.

name: Project Angel Food
description: Delivers free and nutritious meals to individuals battling critical illness.

name: Los Angeles County Bicycle Coalition
description: Promotes cycling for a healthier, safer, and more sustainable Los Angeles.
